# Build context exclusions for container/Dockerfile.
#
# Scoped to this Dockerfile via the `<dockerfile>.dockerignore` convention rather
# than a repository-root .dockerignore: the root file is global to every build in
# the tree, and the legacy Docker/ setup has its own. This one only governs the
# image built from container/Dockerfile.
#
# Two of these entries are correctness, not just speed:
#
#   .git      117 MB, and it changes on every commit, checkout and fetch -- so
#             including it invalidates the COPY layer (and therefore rosdep, the
#             workspace build and the multi-minute MuJoCo pre-warm behind it)
#             every time git touches anything.
#
#   install/  the workspace is built WITHOUT --symlink-install, so install/ is
#             plain copies of host-built artefacts. Copying a host install space
#             into the image would shadow the container's own build with binaries
#             linked against the host's libraries, and the failure would surface
#             at runtime, far from its cause.
.git
.gitignore
.github
build
install
log
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
.pytest_cache
.superpowers
.claude

# Not needed to build or run the simulation.
pic
*.pdf
*.gv
MUJOCO_LOG.TXT
